MBOMBELA &#8211; Police are investigating Mopani Pharmacy after three people were caught with prescription medication hidden in their vehicle on Friday. The medicine was destined for a hospital in Mozambique which offers children with cardio problems treatment, free of charge.Mozambican citizens, Ms Lucretia Desse Mitilana Manjaxi (48), Mr Orlando Ernesto Chibolico (51) and Mr Ramos Antonio Mabasso (36) were arrested.They appeared in court on Monday on a charge of possession of suspected stolen property.Police and local crime fighters discovered medicine hidden behind the back seat of a vehicle at about 16:00.&nbsp;